# Component Styleguide

- Use the provided `component` generator to scaffold new components. It also supports namespaces:
  - `bin/rails g component Users::Avatar`.
  - Prefer a plural for your namespaces to avoid clashing with your models.
- Put your components into `app/components` and their tests into `test/components`.
- Keep filenames consistent.
- Delete files which you don't need for your component.

## ViewComponent

- Use `ApplicationComponent` as the base class.
- Prefer using slots over configuration via attributes.
- Prefer private methods within components over helpers. Use concerns to share behavior.
- Test your components with view specs.

## Unpoly Compilers

- Use `data-compiler` on the root element and `data-element` to connect your JS logic to the DOM.
- Pass data into components via `up-data`.
- Return a list of destructors from your compiler if necessary: [Unpoly Docs: destructor](https://unpoly.com/enhancing-elements#destructor)
- Consider using a Lookbook preview as the starting point for your Jasmine specs.

## CSS

- Use BEM-style CSS.
- Keep consistent with the naming conventions from the provided generator:
  - We use an abbreviated style that differs from regular BEM.
  - No underscores at all.
  - Modifiers are just `-modifier` without repeating the block name.
